<section class="tg-hero tg-hero--router">
    <div class="tg-container tg-hero-grid">
        <div>
            <span class="tg-eyebrow">One API for the best AI models</span>
            <h1 class="tg-hero-title">Build once.<br><span class="tg-hero-accent">Use the best of AI.</span></h1>
            <p class="tg-hero-subtitle">Reach the leading models for chat, code, reasoning, and vision through one familiar API. Choose a model yourself, or let Auto choose for every request.</p>
            <div class="tg-cta-row">
                <a href="/signup" class="tg-btn tg-btn--primary tg-btn--xl">Start building free <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i></a>
                <a href="https://github.com/TextGeneratorio/text-generator.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="tg-btn tg-btn--ghost tg-btn--xl"><span class="tg-github-mark">⌘</span> View on GitHub</a>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-hero-proof" aria-label="Platform highlights">
                <span><i class="material-icons">check_circle</i> OpenAI compatible</span>
                <span><i class="material-icons">check_circle</i> One credit balance</span>
                <span><i class="material-icons">check_circle</i> Fully open source</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tg-routing-console" aria-label="Live model routing example">
            <div class="tg-console-header"><span><i></i><i></i><i></i></span><strong>Smart route</strong><small>Ready</small></div>
            <div class="tg-console-request"><span class="tg-code-key">Request</span><br><span class="tg-code-string" id="route-prompt">“Review this authentication code for security issues.”</span></div>
            <div class="tg-route-trace">
                <div class="tg-trace-step is-done"><span>01</span><div><strong>Task understood</strong><small>Security · code review · complex</small></div><i class="material-icons">check</i></div>
                <div class="tg-trace-line"></div>
                <div class="tg-trace-step is-done"><span>02</span><div><strong>Best fit selected</strong><small>Strong coding and security reasoning</small></div><i class="material-icons">check</i></div>
                <div class="tg-trace-line"></div>
                <div class="tg-trace-step is-live"><span>03</span><div><strong>GPT-5.6 Sol</strong><small>OpenAI · fallback ready</small></div><em>Selected</em></div>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-console-footer"><span><i class="material-icons">auto_awesome</i> Automatic model selection</span><span>Fallback on</span></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tg-hero-glow tg-hero-glow--one"></div><div class="tg-hero-glow tg-hero-glow--two"></div>
</section>

<section class="tg-provider-strip" aria-label="Supported AI providers">
    <div class="tg-container">
        <div class="tg-strip-heading"><span>One endpoint. {{ provider_count }} leading providers.</span><a href="/providers">Explore the network <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i></a></div>
        <div class="tg-provider-logo-row">
            {% for provider in providers[:10] %}
            <a href="{{ provider.url }}" title="Explore {{ provider.name }} models"><img src="{{ provider.logo_url }}" alt="{{ provider.name }}"><span>{{ provider.name }}</span></a>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="tg-section tg-subscription-section" id="subscription">
    <div class="tg-container">
        <div class="tg-subscription-panel">
            <div class="tg-subscription-copy">
                <span class="tg-kicker">Unlimited subscription</span>
                <h2>Unlimited chat, UI tools, and provider APIs.</h2>
                <p>One subscription unlocks unlimited use across Text Generator: chat in the UI, create with the playground and built-in tools, or call the full provider network through our OpenAI-compatible API.</p>
                <div class="tg-cta-row">
                    <a href="/subscribe" class="tg-btn tg-btn--primary tg-btn--xl">Get unlimited access <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i></a>
                    <a href="/signup" class="tg-btn tg-btn--ghost tg-btn--xl">Start free</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tg-subscription-benefits" aria-label="Unlimited subscription benefits">
                <article><i class="material-icons">forum</i><div><strong>Unlimited chat and UI use</strong><span>Use chat, the playground, and built-in creation tools without counting credits.</span></div></article>
                <article><i class="material-icons">hub</i><div><strong>Every API provider</strong><span>Reach the supported provider network from one endpoint with unlimited API access.</span></div></article>
                <article><i class="material-icons">toll</i><div><strong>Credits are still optional</strong><span>Prefer pay as you go? Buy API credits with no subscription required.</span></div></article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="tg-section tg-section--white tg-auto-section">
    <div class="tg-container">
        <div class="tg-catalog-heading">
            <div><span class="tg-kicker tg-kicker--light">Automatic model selection</span><h2>You describe the work.<br>Auto picks the model.</h2></div>
            <p>Use one model ID for everyday requests. Auto matches each job with a model suited to its speed, quality, and cost needs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tg-auto-showcase">
            {% set primary_model = featured_models[0] %}
            <a class="tg-auto-primary" href="{{ primary_model.url }}">
                <span class="tg-auto-primary-top"><span class="tg-auto-icon"><i class="material-icons">auto_awesome</i></span><span class="tg-auto-status"><i></i> Recommended</span></span>
                <span class="tg-auto-primary-copy"><small>{{ primary_model.id }}</small><strong>One smart default for most requests.</strong><span>{{ primary_model.description }}</span></span>
                <span class="tg-auto-primary-example"><small>Example route</small><span><b>Complex code review</b><i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i><b>GPT-5.6 Sol</b></span></span>
                <span class="tg-auto-primary-link">Explore Auto <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i></span>
            </a>
            <div class="tg-auto-list">
                {% for model in featured_models[1:] %}
                <a class="tg-auto-list-item" href="{{ model.url }}">
                    <span class="tg-auto-icon"><i class="material-icons">{% if model.auto_profile == 'code' %}code{% elif model.auto_profile == 'vision' %}visibility{% elif model.auto_profile == 'reasoning' %}psychology{% elif model.auto_profile == 'fast' %}bolt{% elif model.auto_profile == 'cheap' %}savings{% else %}route{% endif %}</i></span>
                    <span><strong>{{ model.name }}</strong><small>{{ model.description }}</small></span>
                    <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i>
                </a>
                {% endfor %}
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tg-auto-benefits"><span><i class="material-icons">check</i>No model comparison</span><span><i class="material-icons">check</i>Provider fallback included</span><span><i class="material-icons">check</i>Exact model choice whenever you need it</span></div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="tg-section tg-platform-section">
    <div class="tg-container tg-platform-grid">
        <div class="tg-platform-copy"><span class="tg-kicker tg-kicker--light">Built for production</span><h2>Your model layer, under control.</h2><p>Use an exact model when consistency matters. Choose Auto when you want quality, speed, and price balanced for you.</p><a href="/docs" class="tg-text-link">Read the API docs <i class="material-icons">arrow_forward</i></a></div>
        <div class="tg-capability-grid">
            <article><i class="material-icons">swap_horiz</i><h3>Built-in fallbacks</h3><p>Keep requests moving when a provider is rate-limited or unavailable.</p></article>
            <article><i class="material-icons">account_balance_wallet</i><h3>One credit balance</h3><p>Fund once, use every routed model, and keep usage in one account.</p></article>
            <article><i class="material-icons">key</i><h3>Your keys or ours</h3><p>Use the managed gateway now and retain a clean path to provider keys.</p></article>
            <article><i class="material-icons">visibility_off</i><h3>Private by design</h3><p>Model selection happens without sending your prompt through another AI call.</p></article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="tg-section tg-section--white">
    <div class="tg-container tg-api-showcase">
        <div class="tg-code-window">
            <div class="tg-code-tabs"><span class="is-active">Python</span><span>JavaScript</span><em>OpenAI SDK</em></div>
            <pre><code><span class="tg-code-purple">from</span> openai <span class="tg-code-purple">import</span> OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    base_url=<span class="tg-code-green">"https://api.text-generator.io/v1"</span>,
    api_key=<span class="tg-code-green">"YOUR_API_KEY"</span>,
)

response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model=<span class="tg-code-green">"text-generator/auto"</span>,
    messages=[{<span class="tg-code-green">"role"</span>: <span class="tg-code-green">"user"</span>,
               <span class="tg-code-green">"content"</span>: <span class="tg-code-green">"Ship something great"</span>}],
)</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div><span class="tg-kicker tg-kicker--light">A two-line migration</span><h2>Keep the SDK.<br>Change the destination.</h2><p>Point the OpenAI client at Text Generator and unlock the provider network without rewriting your application.</p><ul class="tg-check-list"><li><i class="material-icons">check</i>Chat completions and streaming-compatible responses</li><li><i class="material-icons">check</i>Aliases, Auto profiles, and exact model IDs</li><li><i class="material-icons">check</i>Routing metadata and provider response headers</li></ul><a href="/signup" class="tg-btn tg-btn--primary tg-btn--xl">Create a free API key</a></div>
    </div>
</section>

